FT  10 DEC 94 / Weekend Money (Investing for Growth): Eclipse Blinds
Eclipse Blinds is showing the results of new management and a commitment to
one product: window blinds, writes Directus. Directors have bought
consistently since the summer. During that time Eclipse has outperformed the
market by almost 60 per cent.
The largest sale of the week came at Life Sciences International in the
Healthcare sector - it makes equipment for the research and clinical market.
Mark Sketchley, a non-executive director, sold more than 186,000 shares at
143p, two-thirds of his holding.
